The paper discusses a network-assisted protocol for device-to-device (D2D) communication, which involves proximity discovery and direct communication between proximate devices. This falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a power control scheme for underlay communication, which involves multiuser decoding capabilities, and thus falls under information theory (cs.IT). The protocol involves monitoring and announcing devices, which can be seen as a system or control theory problem (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of downlink transmissions, which can be related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the reliability of the protocol, which can be seen as a security and cryptography problem (cs.CR).
